Validations:
    - AngularJS Supports form validations.

    - "$error" is the predefined Object used to store the form related errors.

    - when ever "error raised" in form automatically stores into $error object.


Ex.
    <form name="myForm">
        <label>Uname.</label>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;
        <input type="text"
               name="uname"
               ng-model="uname"
               ng-minlength="3"
               ng-maxlength="6"
               required>

        <h5 style="color:red" ng-if="myForm.uname.$error.minlength">***Minimum 3 characters are required***</h5>
        <h5 style="color:red" ng-if="myForm.uname.$error.maxlength">***Maximum 6 Characters are Allowed***</h5>
        <h5 style="color:red" ng-if="myForm.uname.$error.required && myForm.uname.$dirty">***Can't Left Blank***</h5>
    </form>

Email Validation:
-----------------

<input type="email"
       name="uemail"
       ng-model="uemail"
       required>

<h5 style="color:red" ng-if="myForm.uemail.$error.email">***Please enter the valid email***</h5>
<h5 style="color:red" ng-if="myForm.uemail.$error.required && myForm.uemail.$dirty">***Can't Left Blank***</h5>



Number Validation:
-----------------
<input type="text"
       name="uphone"
       ng-model="uphone"
       ng-pattern="/^[0-9]{10,10}$/;"
       required>

<h5 style="color:red" ng-if="myForm.uphone.$error.required && myForm.uphone.$dirty">***Can't Left Blank***</h5>
<h5 style="color:red" ng-if="myForm.uphone.$error.pattern">***Please Enter the Valid Phone Number***</h5>



Validations by using ngMessages Module
--------------------------------------
    - ngMessages is the predefined module in angularjs, and used to overcome the data redundancy.

    - we can download the "ngMessages Module" by using following bower key.

        "angular-messages"


1. download the ngMessages Module by using bower.

2. add the ngMessages Dependency.

3. create the validation messages by using ng-message directive.

Ex.
    messages.html

<div ng-message="minlength">***Minimum 3 Characters are Required****</div>
<div ng-message="maxlength">****Can't Enter Morethan 6 characters****</div>
<div ng-message="required">***Can't Left Blank***</div>
<div ng-message="email">***Please Enter the Valid Email***</div>
<div ng-message="pattern">***Please Enter the Valid Phone Number***</div>


4. import the validations by using mgMessages Directives.

<div ng-messages="myForm.uname.$error">
    <div ng-messages-include="messages.html"></div>
</div>






















